item.title: back at it
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: I am in denial that this day has come. I'm sad the kids are going back to school, I'm sad I'm heading back to work. I'm sad to have to wake up to an alarm again and to say goodbye to the slow, long mornings. I'm going to miss all the fun and all the time spent with my favorite people.

item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily

Mitch was hoping to see the game live in the stadium but instead we brought the stadium fun to us - we served stadium food for dinner and enjoyed a custom Alabama cookie cake for dessert. A much needed treat to take the sting away from the teams loss.

item.title: string concert
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Every year in January all the schools in our town come together to put on a joint orchestra concert. This performance is intended to show the lower grades how their skills develop over the years if they continue to play their instruments. It is always impressive to see the progress the students and we walked away amazed at the talent in the high school orchestra.

item.title: happy birthday mitchy
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: To our wonderful boy on your 12th birthday… Yep, it’s that time of year again. Another year around the sun, another birthday, another letter from your parents! Now, we are still a few inches away from looking each other eye-to-eye as you have yet to grow into those big feet of yours - but, you are decidedly your own person: smart, loving, sarcastic, and often ridiculous. You are kind and sensitive. Driven and focused, and fueled by any sort of competition - card games, sports, who’s room is cleaner, who can bake a better cupcake. If it can become a competition, you’re in! You are loyal and dedicated, and easily frustrated when others aren’t giving 100%. Some days, you seem wise beyond your years and so much more mature than a twelve-year-old should be. The next minute, you struggle to open a Gatorade bottle or share a sixth grade level joke (that is funny only to you) and, once again, all's right with the world. You are a performer. You are always singing - in the shower, getting dressed, at the dinner table, and the volume constantly rises as though you are performing on a stage for 12,000 people. We've scaled back performances at the dinner table and requested a lower volume throughout the house when your sister is sleeping. But, even then, the struggle is real for you! Your love for basketball is all-consuming and we happily continue drive you to practices and to games so long as you continue to take your smelly basketball clothes to the laundry room, because with age comes things like the start of teen boy funk. Just yesterday, you were our toddler, throwing the ball to Molly in the yard with popsicle juice dripping down your belly.  Today, we’re packing to-go-meals, mapping out sports locations, and in constant “go-go-go” mode with you.  Just yesterday, you were circling the cul-de-sac near our house in Washington on your bike, shouting, “Look I'm going fast like Dinoco”. Today you ride your bike around the neighborhood and meet up with friends to head to the local ice cream store for a scoop of your favorite flavor, banana. (Side Note: Your love for bananas runs deep. We buy at least 24 bananas a week!)  Just yesterday, we were in deep discussions about garbage trucks and airplanes. Today, you talk sports, particularly basketball, like it’s your business. How you know every player in every league, I’ll never know but if you could put that level of attention into remembering to pack away the blanket in the living room, we’d be happy parents. As you grow up, it’s hard to let go, to let you walk your own path and to let you make your own mistakes because in so many ways, you’re still our little boy. But, we can see the amazing person you are becoming, and are so very proud! Happy birthday, big guy. We hope twelve is going to be an amazing year for you! xo Mom&Dad Flashback to this time, 12 years ago...

item.title: 1 year home
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: One year ago today, Mark and I drove two hours each way to pick up a little ball of fur and welcome her into our family. Maple had the biggest belly and cried the entire car ride. While her belly has gone down in size, the crying is still a constant. It's been a fun year full of exhaustion and laughter but in the end, it's the two smiles on each side of Maple that make this experience worth it. The journey of life is far sweeter when shared with a dog!

item.title: birthday day unfolded
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Goodnight 11 year old. While we decorated Mitchy's room for his birthday we had an extra helper on hand. She didn't understand why she wasn't allowed to jump on Mitchell's bed and checked every gift to ensure there wasn't any dog cookies under the wrapping paper. Mitchell was up bright and early on his birthday, hoping we'd be equally excited for his 5:30am wake up. After he was sent back to bed, we gave in around 6:30am, woke up Matilda and headed straight for the gifts! Then it was our usual breakfast routine before heading out to school. Before school, I snuck an empty lunch bag in Mitchell's backpack with a note. The note read "oh no, no lunch! Better head to the office after music." There he found a large brown paper bag with a special take-out lunch and 12 cupcakes for the 12 year old to share with this friends. But I couldn't just leave it at that. I had to hide a happy face balloon inside the bag that came flying out when he opened it. Mitch said this unexpected surprise was very cool! In the evening we had Mitchell's favorite dinner -- steak, baked potatoes and green beans and we wrapped up the evening with his favorite ice cream (banana!) topped with a singing basketball candle! Happy birthday 12 year old.

item.title: Portland Basketball Tournament - Day 0
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We went up to Portland for President's Day weekend so that Mitch could play in the Nike Tournament. If you had told me 2 years ago that I would be going with a 6th grader to a basketball tourney for the long weekend, I would have told you that you were crazy! This was Mitch's first big tournament in D1 and he was pretty nervous, as well as pretty excited. Day 1 We traveled up early on Friday morning so we could visit the Nike store (thanks Illysa) and do the Nike tour (thanks Prime Parents). The employee store was a lot of fun, although Mitch was pretty bummed that they didn't do customized shoes. Everything less 40% thanks to our old baby sitter, nanny, and "adopted" daughter -- Ilyssa. Mitch was probably more excited shopping for his sister! (he sure missed Tilly) After that, we were off the Nike tour. We met up with all the other Prime families and had a great tour of the facility. The kids absolutely loved shooting around at the Nike gym. Prime 6th Grade Gold was ready to play! The team then met up at the gym for some shoot around time before getting in the zone for the tournament which started the next day.

item.title: Portland Basketball Tournament - Day 1
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: After all the excitement, Saturday was here. Nike Tournament here we come! We had two games on Saturday and we knew that we needed to win both to ensure we would play on Monday. Mitch woke up with energy and he was READY TO COMPETE! But first, we needed the tourney sweatshirt. Warmups Underway! We won the first game by 2...Whew - Mitch played great. He really came and competed, and drove What to do. Oh yes. Sugar celebration! Off to Voodoo Donuts. Game 2! -- Oakland Soldiers Yes, we went all the way to Portland to play Oakland Soldiers -- No I am not bitter! We were blown out by Oakland Soldiers 34-10. Mitch got MVP and Coach Frankie told the team that he was the only one who had come to play. But it was a very tough game to watch. Our team just didn't play hard, they had given up, intimidated by "Soldiers" A pretty sad end to day 1, means Day 2 we can't lose another game or there will be nothing to do on Monday. The team put on their pouty faces and off we went for Pizza

item.title: Portland Basketball Tournament - Day 2 (oh Happy Birthday to me!)
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We woke up early on Sunday, Mitch gave me my birthday cards (sad to be away from everyone for my birthday) and we were off to our first game. We were going to play Seattle Rotary Style. We heard they were a tough team but we knew we had to win to stay in the tournament. We came to play and at the end of the half the score was 17-16. Yes, we can still win this game. But after the break we fell apart and lost 47-19 (yes we only scored 3 points in the whole of the second half).  There goes Monday.... For our final game we played West Linn Select and came away with the win. Overall we had a ton of fun playing but wished were not out of the tournament. In the PM we were able to secure employee discount to the Adidas store. (50% off) Shopping therapy works!

item.title: Portland Basketball Tournament - Day 3
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: After a great breakfast, we went and watched the championship games. We had a great weekend, learned a lot, made some new friends, and brought back some amazing memories.. Thanks Buckie... PS. We missed the girls so much on this trip, but I am sure they would have been bored out of their minds!

item.title: st patrick's day
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Well, the trapped somewhat worked. The Leprechaun's left Matilda treats in her trap but destroyed our house. They toilet papered the living room, playroom and the kids room and left rainbows throughout the entire house including inside the toilets. UGH -- why do we run into this nonsense every.single.year!

item.title: tag
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Maple loves playing tag with the kids. To play the game, she grabs a toy and races past them. That's her signal for them to get up and chase her. When the chase her, they have to tag her on her back and run along side of her keeping one hand on her back. This usually results in the kids crashing into the sofa or table and of course sparks a lot of giggles.

item.title: birthday trip
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: For my birthday this year Mark asked what I wanted. It was simple answer for me, "I want to take a trip with my family. And not just any trip, a trip that will remain in my heart forever". This past week we set out on an adventure that was beyond what I had hoped for, beyond what I had imagined, beyond my dreams. It was perfect in every way... (except for the part that I had to return home!)

item.title: Sayulita - travel day
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Today was a travel day. We flew out of Oakland in the morning and arrived in Sayulita around 2pm. Enough time to stop at the store, become acclimated with the house and make our way day to the beach for the sunset. The beach looks good on these two cute kids!

item.title: sayulita - day 1
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Today was spent walking on the beach with our morning coffee, breakfast at the house, back to the beach for body surfing, pool then beach, back to the house for dinner, back to the beach to watch the sunset and finally to bed with sandy hair and full hearts. Mitchy loved the ocean. Anytime his toes hit the water, he had the biggest smile on his face.

item.title: sayulita - day 2
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: The days started to become a blur, time slowed down, we got into a route and all just felt right in the world. We started a habitat for crabs, played on the beach (again!), napped, ... it was truly heaven on earth! This wonderful husband of mine made all my dreams come true on this trip. However, I secretly think with all his pool side napping he did, he loved every minute too! Could life be any more perfect?! Matilda sat cuddling the crabs, everyday.

item.title: sayulita - day 2, part 2
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: With many trips to the beach, I have lots of wave riding photos. These two had the best time together. Mark and I joked in the ocean it looked like they were in the spin cycle of the washing machine. It was so fun seeing them enjoy natures playground!

item.title: sayulita - day 3 - ziplining
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: The kids each had an item on their "trip-list". Mitchell wanted to try zip-lining through the jungle. Today we took a break from one trip to the beach to head to the jungle but then we returned to regular scheduled programming, beach combing!

item.title: sayulita - day 3, part 2
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We made our way to a popular surf beach today and had lots of fun paying in the ocean and riding the waves!

item.title: sayulita - day 4
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: More of the same, living our best life -- collecting more crabs, a quick ride into town on the golf cart for bracelets, BBQ in the backyard and a beach sunset. Matilda sleeping in! This is Mitchy with Kai. Kai is 8months old and lives in the main house. He met us every morning for our coffee walk on the beach. They'd put on clothes to start the day and end up in the water. It never failed. Mark couldn't understand why they didn't just start with their swimsuits. Football on the beach, Mitchy's 2nd favorite thing to do next to playing in the ocean. Matilda loved her crabs. She named them for the days she adopted them. She had Sunday, Monday, Tuesday and Mundane. Monday eventually escaped which prevented Matilda from adding more to the lot. We aren't sure how Mundane got its name but that crab turned out to be a favorite amongst all. Except for Mark who was a crab-activist and chanted "free the crabs" everyday! Matilda worked with this street vendor to customize 5 bracelets for her friends. I panicked the entire 20minutes were were in town, praying no one got sick after this little adventure that wasn't suppose to be allowed. Mark drove us around in this little golf cart like a crazy man. He also treated me to beach towels for my birthday but set a limit of no more than 6 beach towels. To this day, I still wish I had 12. We BBQ'd every night. The first night we used the golf cart lights since we couldn't find the string lights switch. After a bit of help the next day, the BBQ boys were back in action with additional lights for grill with!

item.title: sayulita - day 5
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Today we played at the beach, swam in the pool, made homemade pizzas in the pizza oven with Edgar and rode horses on the beach at sunset. Matilda's "trip-list" wish that she wasn't too sure about after the ride! Mark on the other hand showed us all up with his galloping skills and his horse conversations along the trail. Every trip they paint watercolors of their memories. This is a truly gift for me as I save them to remember what touched their hearts. Mark's horse was named Lobo. Lobo liked to snack on everything on the trail. Matilda rode Panini, Mitchell rode Speedy and I rode a grumpy old horse who drooled the entire ride and bucked Mark's horse because he was too close! We saw whales breaching at sunset. It was amazing and so much fun. After dark we'd head back to the house, cuddle under blankets and look at the stars together.

item.title: sayulita - day 6
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Today was our last day and in between my fits of tears Mark said it was my day to choose what we did so I chose nothing and we did just that. We stayed at the house, played at the beach, swam in the pool and soaked up every last minute of this amazing place. (Mark did however, dig the biggest sand hole and buried the kids, but other than that, we pretty much did nothing!) This kid never sleeps in. Lots of play time in the ocean tired this guy out! I spent a lot of time in this little kitchen preparing meals for the family. I loved it! She builds things out of anything anywhere! Seeing all these swimsuits, drying out daily brought the biggest smile to my face. We were given fresh coconuts on the beach to drink. It was delicious! These two are the best people on the planet!

item.title: goodbye sayulita
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: The day I dreaded all week had come. It was time to say good-bye, head back to reality and chalk this trip up as our best trip yet! We left for the airport early and stopped in Puerto Vallarta for lunch, then home. Matilda loved all the seafood in Mexico. That and the people that would walk buy and sell her bracelets at the table. Worst photo of the entire trip. At the airport, enroute home.

item.title: earrings
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Matilda has been talking about getting earrings for a few months now. On Sunday we had a slow morning so we asked her if she wanted to get her ears pierced!  She was surprised and nervous but said yes right away. We all hopped in the car and within two hours we had a girl with sweet little earrings in her ears. Matilda was so brave through the entire process and is very happy with her earrings.

item.title: march madness
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We always look forward to March madness and were ready for the big dance to begin this year. Mitchy picked his team (Duke) months in advance but the rest of us held out and waiting to make our final choices. Mark and I couldn't be more thrilled that our team, Virginia made it all the way clinching the championship. And to think Mitchy questioned our choices in the beginning... we need to teach this kid a thing or two about brackets!

item.title: lacrosse weekend

item.title: CMEA
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: The California Music Education Association hosts a festival each year to give schools in the area a chance to perform and complete against each other to help develop their music through feedback. Mitchell's 6th grade orchestra class performed three songs and then were provided music they had never seen before and were given 5minutes to read the music and perform. Across the board, Mitchell's class received "excellence" in their performances. Quite an accomplishment given this is only their first year performing at CMEA and their musical skills are still developing. This event was quite inspirational to Mitchell and us all! Proud of our little guy.

item.title: easter eggs

item.content:encoded: Coloring Easter eggs in preparation for Easter. These two told me today, they are older and need to be challenged in their egg dying skills. Next year I better add to my art supplies options for egg designs!

item.content:encoded: Mitchell and Matilda woke up to a note from the Easter Bunny and eggs hidden all over the house. But there wasn't candy inside the eggs, there were puzzle pieces and they had to put together the puzzle to decode the message and find their Easter baskets.

item.title: easter

item.title: lacrosse

item.title: field day

item.title: mother's day
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: These three have my whole heart. I am thankful everyday that I get to learn from them and be their Mom.

item.title: volleyball
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: This weekend was Matilda's last volleyball game for the season.  Her team played three games in the finals and won two of their games. Matilda played really well and had a lot of fun. She's already told me she's playing again next year!

item.title: tech rehearsal
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily

item.title: open house

item.title: reno
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: These two are Reno-bound this weekend for a basketball tournament. Go Mitchy -- The game isn't over until the click hits 00:00 -- play hard and compete! Since it was just the boys we lose out on having the team photographer there and capturing every moment, but we were able to capture a few treasures.. On the road up we always stop in Truckee for lunch.. twice in a row we have stopped at Bar of America. Although the bar does look pretty good we both recommend the fish and chips and fish tacos! We stayed at the same place this year.. good old Peppermill! Super expensive but we "usually" the whole team stays in the same place.. not this year! We found out too late but the rest of his team stayed in Sparks.. Next year need to stay where the team stays... more fun for the guy!   First things first! Dinner at Ruby's Steakhouse! Followed by evening practice (9pm practice .. where is my cocktail!) The boys had fun shooting around and before long we were tournament bound... Step 1: Get the gear! Step 2: Play some Ball Step 4: Lament on coming 3rd -- no prize for coming 3rd! Although I was very proud of the team. Playing D1 and being close to 2nd place (lost by 1 point) they did us proud!. My little buckie played his heart out!

item.title: Seussical
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Matilda stared in her last elementary school theatre production of Seussical. She was Mayzie la Bird. She was sassy and free, enough about Horton let's talk about Mayzie! I was so very proud of Matilda and loved sitting in the audience, watching her shine on stage. And she had the best costume on stage so there was no missing her! Thanks to all Matilda's fans who came to see the show. She loved all the encouragement and support.

Everyone had a lot of fun, including Maple who would jump in the pool anytime the kids jumped in! 7th graders! 6th graders!

item.title: end of year surprise
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: All year long the kids gave it their all, they worked hard and poured their heart, sweat, and tears into their school. They set high standards for themselves and constantly embodied what we value -- school first (always) keeping laser-focused on their academics. Mitchell and Matilda both loved learning, participated in events and took on every opportunity that was presented to them. Mark and I sat down, reflected on the year and thought of something special we would like to do for the kids. We wanted the kids to understand their hard work demonstrated by their grades didn't go unnoticed by us. We want to continue to encourage them to push hard and work hard but also show them that successes should be celebrated! So, this year we wrapped two gifts in customized paper complete with notes and memories from us of the year. The kids loved reading each part and laughed about the things we chose to highlight! This little demonstration of love and appreciation is a tradition Mark and I look forward to each year. Mitchy and Tilly -- Excellent work! You both make us very proud. Most importantly, your hard work makes yourself proud. Continue to reach for the stars, you both have the entire world at your fingertips. Mark choose an LED robot for Matilda to enjoy and play with over the summer, coding. They two of them have been bickering all morning. Sharing is rough with two people and only one robot!

item.title: Happy 15th Anniversary to the one I love..
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Honey - I can’t believe it but we have only been married for 15 years. It feels like you have always been part of my life. As we take time to reflect on the last 15 years and plan for the next 15,000 I want you to know how much you mean to me. You mean everything to me, you are my friend, my wife, and yes sometimes my pain in the "you know where” but, I wouldn't change you for the world! We don’t always agree, but we always find a way to get past those disagreements. You are a wonderful mom. You always say you need more “diamonds” but you have two of the most precious children the world has ever had. You find joy in interacting with them, you're patient, caring, and the sacrifices you make for them is something I will never get tired of watching. You were born to be a mom, and you are truly the best mom in the world. To our furry friend your soft side comes out, you let your guard down and I see another side of you. The protector of the “baby dog”, the proud mama bear, but also the total softy. I laugh when I see how Maple gets everything she wants - she sure has you beat. Keep being who you are, you're great at it!

item.title: water park
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Today was a day to let the kids be wild and be kids. While I don't always choose these places, it was time to make some memories that the kids would choose and a surprise trip to the water turned out to be the best day of their lives (haha)!

item.title: Father's day dinner
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: This is my 2nd year of taking my Dad out to dinner for Father's Day. It is really fun to treat my Dad because it's my way of giving back to him for all that he does for me. This year we went to a Brazilian steakhouse. They gave us a card with red on one side and green on the other. If you wanted more you kept the green side up. If you were full, you had the red side up. I think Dad really liked this place because his card was always green. I couldn't keep up! Love you Dad. -Mitch

item.title: mary poppins
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: I love watching the kids perform on stage and this summer we sat in the audience for another performance to watch Matilda in Mary Poppins. Matilda sang and danced and smiled from ear to ear on stage. We were so proud!

item.title: mammoth
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We enjoyed our family vacation to Mammoth two years ago and felt there was so we had yet to see that another trip was in order. We packed up the truck and headed to one of the most beautiful places on Earth. Day one, the journey. But when your journey takes you through Yosemite, it's never a bad day!

item.title: mammoth - day 1
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We decided a hike was in order for day one so we headed to Mosquito Flats to hike Little Lakes Valley to Gem Lakes. Over eight miles of hiking, 1,000 ft of climbing, beautiful views, and a side of moaning from the mini hikers but we completed what we set out to complete and had sore feet to show for it!

item.title: mammoth - day 2
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Today we decided to rest our feet, enjoy a boat ride around Lake Mary and then a ride down Lake Mary's Road from Horseshoe Lake before we settled in for an evening of homemade pasta and a long round of Monopoly.

item.title: mammoth - day 3
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Back to hiking! This time we headed towards Yosemite almost to the entrance up Tioga Pass to 20 Lakes Basin Loop Trail, what we deemed, Mosquito Lake. The hike was about 5.5 miles for us, 500ft of climbing, which started along Saddleback Lake and headed into the mountains crossing 20 lakes. As we started our climb to the summit the mosquitos were awful. If we stood for a minute, we were attacked. I told Mark we were missing something when everyone heading back our way on the hike all had mosquito masks. We thought they weren't on trend, when really we were the losers! At one point Mitchy said to us, "this isn't fun" and we said, "you're right, we're going back." Mark threw on his diy mosquito net, left the rest of us to fend for ourselves and away we went, back to the car with a lot of bits to show for our adventure. Good thing there was a ice cream stand on the side of the highway and we were able to treat ourselves to mike shakes that we could enjoy while we itched!

item.title: mammoth - day 4
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Another day off from hiking, the kids favorite type of days! Today we rode the town trolly and braved the gondola up to the top of Mammoth Mountain. The views were spectacular. We then spent the afternoon enjoying the sun at the bottom of the mountain while the kids tackled the ropes course!

item.title: mammoth - day 5
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Last full day of vacation. Everyone was sad. We all had such a good time, we wished we could stay longer and hoped this day wouldn't come quickly. Luckily, earlier in the week, after our 1st boat ride, Mark read about another lake, Convict Lake, where you could rent a boat AND bonus, the boat came with a BBQ! Who wouldn't want to spend their last day on the lake, enjoying the views, while having a BBQ? I dialed the phone and booked a boat as quickly as I could and booked a boat. Boy was that the best decision we made - we all loved our last day and Matilda said it was the best day of her life!!! We spent the day touring the lake, enjoying lunch (which we shared with a few canoe'rs on the lake!), boat dancing to our music (thanks for modern day technology!) and hanging together sharing laughs while making memories. A perfect day! And then Matilda convinced Mark and John to find a rope to pull her behind the boat and the rest is history (maybe this is where the best day of her life came in!).

item.title: goodbye mammoth
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: The day has arrived, it's time to say good bye. Time to make the trek home and hold the sweet memories made close to our hearts. While it may take many months to move past my sadness of vacation coming to an end, I thank my lucky stars everyday that I get to do life with these wonderful people. Until next time....

item.title: happy birthday mom
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: I believe birthdays should be celebrated and I also believe milestone birthdays call for an extra celebration! Over the last year John, Melissa and I have been quietly planning, scheming, organizing a special weekend for my Mom. The day finally arrived, we packed our bags and headed to the beach for a few relaxing days of family and fun. But we couldn't miss adding in a few birthday festivities such as coffee door drops, pull up competitions, daily smoke fires, watercolors on the back patio, tear filled speeches from the littles, and much much more. Happy birthday Mom!

item.content:encoded: After the school dance on Friday night, when you get the call asking if a few friends can come swimming you say "yes" then dash to shuttle the kids to the house, race to the store to buy food, convince your husband to fire up the grill to feed the growing boys and help drag the kids out of the pool at 10pm so they can go to bed -- all of this chaos makes for a fun evening had by all!!!

item.title: soccer

She was so determined to get a goal there was no stopping her attacking the net. As we were leaving the game one of her teammates told her "I'm certain I know who is going to get the golden ball this game!" as she smiled at Matilda. If my vote is anything to go by, Matilda's performance in the game was definitely deserving of the golden ball!!!

item.title: happy birthday matilda
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Matilda, Chica, Bean, Tills, Tilda, MJ, Tida-J, Sissy, Buggy, Porky, Tilly, Matilda Jay, …, Today you are 11. Awk, 11! We know you hear this daily and today should be no different - you are growing up far too quickly for our parental hearts. Our little chocolate milk loving girl is growing to be one of the most amazing humans on the planet and wow are we lucky to be part of your world. Matilda, at 11 you are; brave, kind, curious, funny, smart, resourceful, patient, stubborn, determined and a lover of the simple pleasures in life - notebooks, pencils and pens! During your 11 years on Earth we have gifted you several names. What started with the name you were given when born, Matilda Jay, has morphed in many directions. We often discuss who has the most amount of additional names in the family and you are always win the top award! These names changes are very fitting for you as you are full of life and always keep us on our toes. You have transitioned into middle school with ease. You have taken on the additional responsibility, workload, and complexity of middle school friendships without missing a beat. You finish your homework before we can even ask and you’re on your computer before the sun comes up making sure you didn’t miss an assignment overnight. We often have to remind ourselves of your true age as you carry yourself with such confidence and poise and are wise beyond your years. It’s no secret to anyone that has seen you recently, you have grown tall. You are now taller than your brother, have restocked your closet twice in the last six months, and now share a wardrobe with your favorite person, Mom! (Much to Mom’s enjoyment and to your dismay.) While this short period of time is here, Mom’s taking joy in the new younger fashion trends she can partake in thanks to your growth and closet! You have also become our resident computer expert, whether it is checking our phone usage, fixing your brother's computer, or setting up yet another Fitbit -- you are always there lending a hand. Never stop challenging yourself, never stop challenging us - OK maybe stop challenging Dad, just a little! ;-) You have become an amazing dog whisperer, and our little Maple loves you with her whole heart. We always laugh at the number of times we find her in your room, sleeping on your bed. Maple adores you and you adore her. Keep enjoying this amazing bond you have with your puppy. As you enter your 11th year around the sun we want you to know how special you are to our family and how much we love you. Happy birthday to our best girl! We ALL love you lots. -Dad, Mom, Mitchy & Maple

item.title: shanghai birthday
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Last week I received a note from one of Tilly's friends, Mom. The girls asked if they could Shanghai Tills for her birthday. What this means is that the girls show up to our house before school, surprise Tilly, and bring clothes for her to wear to school that are a bit silly. While Mark and I knew this wouldn't be Matilda's most favorite thing, we also knew how much this meant to the girls and how sweet their intentions were to do something special for Tills so we said "yes". Bright and early this morning, six girls came through the door shouting 'happy birthday'. Matilda was surprised. The girls whisked Matilda to her room to change. They attempted several outfit suggestions which most Matilda declined, eventually settling in on something they could all agree on. Then it was into the kitchen for breakfast then over to the monkey bars to play before school. When it was time for school, the girls all piled in the truck and suggested we roll down the windows and sing. I was completely fine with this!!! But not only did we sing, we danced, we waved at cars, yelled out the window at kids walking to school. As the girls left the car they said that was so fun and asked if we could do carpool karaoke again next week!

item.title: birthday lunch
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: With the kids both in middle school celebrations are smaller so for their birthdays we decided we'd surprise them with their favorite lunch. We send a note in their lunchbox saying "oh no, no lunch, better check the office" and much to their surprise, in the office is a lunch delivery and a balloon just for them. This year we picked up Matilda's favorite, pot stickers and cupcakes. Hoping these little memories are ones they keep close to their hearts as they grow up. This year Matilda has a school field trip on her birthday so she had all her birthday celebrations. Birthday girl coming home on the bus with her shanghai outfit and birthday lunch leftovers!

item.title: dry ice fruit
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Mitchell came home from science class inspired to try a video his teacher shared; putting fruit and dry ice together in a cooler to taste the carbonation in the fruit after it sits for 12-14 hours. When the kids come home inspired and excited to learn something new, I'm always in favor of supporting their interests. Mitch said our local grocery store had dry ice so we added that to our shopping list and this week tried out the experiment. What started out as a fun exercise for the kids, turned into entertainment for Mark and I watching the kids battle with saran wrap. We'll be doing lots more activities with saran-wrap and oversized gloves in the future when I feel I need a good laugh. During the experiment Mark introduced the kids to dry ice in water, which of course they loved!

item.title: birthday morning unfolded
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Every year we get birthday ready with Mark and I working late into the night to prep for the celebrations that come early the next morning. I always have a plan and supplies ready for the decorating and Mark comes in strong during birthday-prep to help me. This year Mark was about ready to throw my idea out the window. After quite sometime sitting in front of Matilda's door dropping balloon after balloon he was over all of my idea, over me and spitting comments in a low voice directed at me! BUT, look at this awesome door!!! How cool is to wake up and have balloons fall all over you when you open your door??? What a surprise!!! Or, 15 minutes after Mark finishes the project? Yep! Just before midnight as Mark crawled into bed and put his head on the pillow he said "there she is. she's awake" Sure enough, Matilda had woken up to go to the bathroom which she NEVER does!!! But tonight of all nights she did. There they were, balloons falling on her at midnight - happy birthday Tills! Here's the birthday girl at 545am. She was finally able to turn on the light and figure out what she got herself into at midnight. Let's start the present party - Matilda's been looking forward to this moment for months. Especially the last week with her birthday count down chart she made. Mark did quite the wrap job on Matilda's gifts. He mixed boxes around, took gift pieces apart, wrapped some items in layers and layers of packing tape, basically did everything to make things difficult. Opening gifts was a chore for Matilda and left both her and Mitchell confused on what her actual gifts were. A cell phone, (which was her big gift) after she unwrapped had Matilda and Mitchell thinking it was fake, possibly a notebook, just a screen photo? They had no clue what it was but thought it was a big joke until Mitch pushed the 'on' button and the phone lit up! A birthday she was hoping for quite some time...

item.title: school field trip
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Matilda is off with her science class to Chabot for a field trip today - lunch bag was ready to go. And since it's her birthday today, every food item is wrapped inside the bag with birthday paper, a birthday napkin and a birthday note from her family. Hope our girl enjoys her little surprise from her family who love her very much!

item.title: cotillion
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: In our town 7th grade cotillion is a big deal. Something I had no idea of but quickly learned of the significance after a few discussions so I signed Mitchell up, against his wishes, but he remained positive about how annoying his enrollment was. The 1st cotillion day arrived, the pre-party invites had been accepted and we were jumping in, feet first with no clue what to expect! At the end of the evening, Mitchy said he had a good time. I think when almost the entire 7th grade signs up, it's hard not to have fun!

item.title: birthday dinner
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily

item.title: benihana & ice cream
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: For Matilda's birthday we took a few of her friends out to dinner and ice cream. Mitchell also got to invite a friend to the birthday celebrations but since two of Matilda's friends each have brothers whom are Mitchell's friends, he invited both. So we had three sibling combos (!) and two additional friends along for the fun. Mark took the boys in one car and I took the girls in the big truck. The girls LOVED this. Matilda set up my camera video and for the entire car ride the girls performed for the video. At a light we pulled along side the boys car and they were all VERY thankful they weren't riding with us. I'm not sure why??? We were all having a great time and are quite good at group carpool karaoke!!!! Let's pause and take a look at the photo below. How adorable are these middle school 6th graders? I want to be them when I grow up! Dinner was fun. There were food options for everyone. Everyone liked what they ordered. The chef was great with the kids and very interactive with them. I would like to note however, other than Mark, the Herring kids were 0/2 in their attempts to catch a chicken piece in their mouth. The two other sibling combos all caught their chicken pieces but the Herring kids, failed us!!! I digress... We were loud, wild and laughed a lot but no one seemed to mind. The restaurant was packed and loud so it was perfect with all the noise. The kids all were really fun. Mark and I both enjoyed the evening with all of them. Benihana photo gift. We should have had the iPhone 11 pro wide lens for this!!!

item.title: family hike
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: It isn't often that we have an entire day on the weekend to ourselves. Today we took advantage of the rare opportunity and headed out on a family hike. By the end, the kids were less than thrilled with our hike decision as the last part was quite a steep hill. You can only imagine their excitement when we got home and suggested we all wash the cars. What fun! But let's freeze time for a moment and appreciate this photo. The small window of time when everyone was happy and enjoying the great outdoors together.

item.title: power outage
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: This weekend were hit with our 2nd power outage in the last two weeks. PG&E hoped by shutting down the power lines during warm weather wind storms would prevent fires caused by live wires. This left us with no option but to get creative, pull out our Washington wind storm skills, purchase a generator, a string of rope lights and we were storm ready.

item.title: Gingerbread making with Tills
item.dc:creator: ourfishtilly
item.content:encoded: Yesterday I had six of my girl friends over for some Gingerbread house making. We had lots of fun and of course did LOTS of eating.  The end products were amazing. Some people took the route of one candy for the house and two for my mouth, others route was to try to get as much candy on the house as possible (so that you can eat it later), some tried to get a nice design on their house.   -Tilly

item.title: gingerbread house decorating
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Mitchy decided he wanted to make a gingerbread house too. Since I'd made so many this year already, how could I say no? So I whipped up another house just for him!

item.title: candy cane
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: At the kids school you could send a candy cane gram to someone. Look who got a gram and who sent it to him! Warms my heart when the kids do something special for each other.

item.title: christmas with madison
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Matilda couldn't wait to give Madison her gift she made her for Christmas. She knew how much Madison loved books and thought a book filled with photos of the two of them would be a perfect gift. One night Matilda sat at the computer and designed the entire book - the colors, the font, the layout. It was really sweet to see how much thought and time Matilda put into this gift.

item.title: cookie decorating
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We couldn't wait for another year of cookie decorating with Jason and Tiffany. This year Tiffany came in strong with a pre-planned idea for Yoda that blew us all away! The judging was a bit questionable (as always with Mark judging!) but everyone went home a winner and we had a lot of fun in the process.

item.title: christmas eve day
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: This year for Christmas Eve we headed to the Ft Funston for the afternoon. We had so much fun. Maple ran crazy, the kids froze in the water, and Mark and I enjoyed a quiet walk along the beach. It was the perfect way to start the Christmas festivities.

item.title: christmas eve
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: After our day at the beach we warmed up and spent the evening in our Christmas jammies, kids opening one gift, playing games, venturing out with hot chocolate to see Christmas lights - creating memories one by one!

item.title: therapy exam
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: We have been working to certify Maple as a therapy dog which means she needs to pass a series of test to receive be able to do service work. Today was Maple's first test and we knew going into it that she wasn't likely ready. She still has the jumps when she meets new people but, we thought going through the test would be a good experience to prepare for future tests. The first test portion of the test was sitting while her owner was greeted. For this portion of the exam Maple decided she'd do the greeting herself and then we failed!  Back to more practice, back to retest in a few months.

item.title: technology
item.dc:creator: ourfishfamily
item.content:encoded: Mark and Matilda love technology. They love to quiz each other to see if they know the latest tips and tricks on their devices. Over the break they decided they were going to upgrade the front door so they can lock and unlock the house from anywhere on their devices. Mark and Matilda were so excited about their new toy. I liked the idea up until I saw how huge the unit is on the door but, they tell me it's so cool, there's no changing it back.
